question: Ava has 10 jars of frosting in her storage room. Each jar of frosting can decorate 12 cookies. Ava wants to bake enough cookies to use up all of her frosting. If each rack holds 8 cookies, how many racks worth of cookies should she bake?
answer:
She has enough frosting for 10 * 12 = <<10*12=120>>120 cookies.
She needs 120 / 8 = <<120/8=15>>15 racks to bake all of the cookies.
#### 15
